The paper discusses the implementation aspects of large intelligent surfaces (LISs) for wireless communication systems. It focuses on the radio-frequency circuits and real-time processing viewpoints, which are relevant to the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), augmented reality (cs.AR), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
